# ORIG TITLE    1001 nights to fight AIDS in Vienna . 
# ORIG CONTENT  Vienna’s Life ball, Europe’s biggest AIDS benefit attracted thousands of revellers for its 1001 nights themed party, and the 3,000 euro entry price didn’t appear to put off the VIPs. Last year it raised over 2 million euros, much of which was donated to the Bill Clinton’s initiative to reduce HIV infections among babies in Africa. 
